# Static Routes Configuration
#
# Each line defines a routing rule: <pattern> <action> [priority <n>]
#
# Patterns:
#   ipn:<alloc>.<node>.<service>   Exact or wildcard IPN EID
#   dtn://<node>/<path>            Exact or glob DTN EID
#   Wildcards: * matches any value, [N-M] matches a range
#
# Actions:
#   via <eid>       Forward to next-hop node
#   drop [<code>]   Discard bundle (optional BPv7 reason code)
#   reflect         Return bundle to previous node
#
# Priority:
#   Lower values are checked first. Default from config (typically 100).
#   Use higher values for catch-all rules.
#
# Lines starting with # are comments. Blank lines are ignored.
# Keywords (via, drop, reflect, priority) are case-insensitive.

# Forward all traffic for node 2 via a specific next-hop
ipn:2.*.* via ipn:2.1.0

# Forward all traffic for allocator 3 via a specific peer
ipn:3.*.* via ipn:3.1.0 priority 50

# Drop traffic to a decommissioned node
ipn:4.*.* drop

# Drop with a specific BPv7 reason code (3 = NoKnownRouteToDestinationFromHere)
ipn:99.*.* drop 3

# Reflect unroutable DTN bundles back to sender (low priority catch-all)
dtn://**/** reflect priority 1000

# Route DTN traffic for a specific node
dtn://relay.example/** via dtn://gateway.example/
